            <fr:title text="Path object">Path object</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0010.agda" type="external">erct-0010.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" title="Reflexive graph" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" type="local">reflexive graph</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong>univalent</html:strong></html:em> when for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} x\approx _{\mathcal {A}} y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, or (equivalently), is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" type="local">contractible</fr:link> with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. We shall refer to a univalent <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" title="Reflexive graph" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-004B/" type="local">reflexive graph</fr:link> as a <html:em><html:strong>path object</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
            <html:p>We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {PathObj}]]></fr:tex> for the (large) type of path objects. In our notation, we will at times silently coerce a given path object to its underlying type of vertices.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
